  "description": "A **hardware accelerator** is a specialized processor designed to perform a specific class of computations more efficiently than a general-purpose [digital computer](./digital-computer.md)'s CPU. Efficiency here means some combination of higher throughput, lower latency, or lower power consumption for the target workload.",
